Uses of Package
TestTool.Model.QuestionCreation

  • Packages that use TestTool.Model.QuestionCreation 
    Package Description
    TestTool.Model.QuestionBank
    TestTool.Model.QuestionBank contains the classes that are needed to stores all the questions provided by the user and contain the options needed to sort the questions.
    TestTool.Model.QuestionCreation
    TestTool.Model.QuestionCreation contains the different types of questions available for creation within the Test Tool program.
    TestTool.Model.TestCreation
    TestTool.Model.TestCreation contains the classes that are needed to store all the user settings for creating a basic or an advanced test and also uses and algorithm to generate a random test.
    TestTool.Model.TestGrading
    TestTool.Model.TestGrading contains the objects that are used for grading tests.
    TestTool.Model.TestResults
    This package includes model classes for the test results functions of the Test Tool, including viewing test and question statistics.
  • Classes in TestTool.Model.QuestionCreation used by TestTool.Model.QuestionBank 
    Class and Description
    Question
    A Question contains a type, the literal question, a point value, a subject the question belongs to, its difficulty, the course the question belongs to, the date it's created, and the creator's login
